HEADWORD: Margarite
<hw>Mar"ga*rite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>margarita</ets>, Gr. <?/ a pearl; cf. F.
<ets>marguerite</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A pearl.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Peacham.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral related to the micas,
but low in silica and yielding brittle folia with pearly
luster.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Margaritic</ent>⟦br⟧
